snippet.textDisplay:
I'm sorry to do this. I don't wish to be a complaining fan. I truly just want to sit back and enjoy something entertaining. WWE makes this so hard, sometimes.


The ineptitude of the creative in this segment:
-Cena states he's sitting WM out to let future guys get a shot - in essence, admitting that WWE buries its current generation in favor of the old, part-timers.
-Cena states that WM should be earned, not demanded - in essence, admitting that there needs to be a logical buildup to big matches.
-The Fiend is sent out to DEMAND a match against the old, part-timer only 24 hours after being buried (lopsidedly) by an even older part-timer.


This is WWE wanting to have its cake and eat it too. They do just enough to admit their faults and make it seem like they're listening to the fans. But then they completely back-hand their own statements a mere 3 minutes later and stubbornly stick with a formula that is NOT working.


Do they really think the fans don't see through the hypocrisy and ineptitude? Do they really think that, by feeding these words through an amazing, beloved legend, everyone will turn a blind eye?


This is not a criticism of Cena as he's just doing what he's told to do. This is a criticism of their lack of creativity and poor writing.


Fans ARE seeing right through the bologna. It's why their ratings continue to drop, network subscribers stay low, and their stock is falling.


It's a shame because they're wasting an amazing talented crop of wrestlers.


I don't like to complain. I just want to enjoy. Their product currently just isn't very good. I am rooting for it to improve. I am a fan - and not a sour one.
